node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.text:
Robinhood 🤝 Crypto⁠
⁠
Robinhood said its crypto revenue accounted for more than half of all transaction-based revenue in the second quarter, as retail investors turned to the app for purchases of bitcoin, ethereum and other digital currencies.⁠
⁠
In its first earnings report since its IPO last month, Robinhood said its revenue from crypto transactions was $233 million, up from $5 million in the year-ago quarter. ⁠
⁠
What percentage of cumulative net-funded accounts traded crypto in the quarter? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'U.S. will begin wide distribution of Covid booster shots next month, saying vaccine protection wanes over time CNBC'.

node.text:
🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
The U.S. will begin widely distributing Covid-19 booster shots next month as new data shows that vaccine protection wanes over time, top U.S. health officials announced in a joint statement Wednesday.⁠
⁠
U.S. agencies are preparing to offer booster shots to all eligible Americans beginning the week of Sept. 20, starting 8 months after their second dose of Pfizer or Moderna’s vaccines, officials said. While they said recipients of Johnson & Johnson’s single-shot vaccine will likely need boosters, they are awaiting more data in the next few weeks before making a formal recommendation.⁠
⁠
More details on the decision to recommend booster shots at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'to Investors are starting question whether there really is no alternative to the u.s., BofA finds BOBBY CNBC'.

node.text:
New for subscribers: The notion that the U.S. is practically the only place to invest is intact among professional investors who nonetheless are starting to get concerned about some issues that could derail that trade.⁠
⁠
Respondents to August’s Bank of America Fund Manager Survey are still loaded up on stocks, though they cut allocations by 4 percentage points to a net 54% overweight position, the lowest since July 2020.⁠
⁠
Why do many investors think there is no alternative to U.S. equities? Read more at the link in bio. (Check out CNBC Pro for 7 days for free!)

node.text:
The “Super Bowl” of classic car collecting ended with a roar over the weekend, with auction sales at Monterey and Pebble Beach totaling $345 million, up 35% from 2019.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The top seller of the week, as expected, was a 1995 McLaren F1 sold by Gooding & Co. for $20.5 million, making it the most expensive car to sell at auction since 2018.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
For details on the top 10 cars sold during Monterey Car Week (and how much they sold for), visit the link in bio.

node.text:
The cryptocurrency platform targeted in a massive heist is now inviting the hacker behind it to become an advisor to the firm, and promising a $500,000 reward for the restoration of user funds.⁠
⁠
Poly Network was hit with a major attack last week which saw the hacker, or hackers, make off with more than $600 million worth of tokens. It is thought to be the largest crypto heist of all time. In Poly Network’s case, the hacker has taken the unusual step of returning most of the stolen money. All but $33 million of the crypto has now been returned. ⁠
⁠
Details on if that hacker (dubbed "Mr. White Hat") plans to accept Poly Network's offer at the link in bio.

node.text:
Five states broke records for the average number of daily new Covid cases over the weekend as the delta variant strains hospital systems across the U.S. and forces many states to reinstate public health restrictions.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Florida, Louisiana, Hawaii, Oregon and Mississippi all reached new peaks in their seven-day average of new cases per day as of Sunday, according to a CNBC analysis of data compiled by Johns Hopkins University. On a per capita basis, Louisiana, Mississippi and Florida are suffering from the three worst outbreaks in the country.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Read about the outbreaks in each of these five states at the link in bio. (With @chartoftheday)

node.text:
Ed Yardeni believes the U.S. economy is on the cusp of “nirvana.”⁠
⁠
Despite uncertainty surrounding inflation and Covid-19 variants, the longtime bull believes the pandemic is significantly accelerating corporate America’s adoption of cutting-edge technology designed to expand productivity.⁠
⁠
According to Yardeni, the move is ushering in a modern roaring ’20s on Wall Street.⁠
⁠
What kind of stocks does Yardeni say you should buy? Link in bio to find out.

node.text:
New for subscribers: “The Big Short” investor Michael Burry is betting against Cathie Woods’ ARK Innovation ETF, according to a regulatory filing that revealed a short position via options. 👀⁠
⁠
Burry’s Scion Asset Management bought 2,355 put contracts against the red-hot tech ETF during the second quarter and held them through the end of the quarter. Investors profit from puts when the underlying securities fall in prices.⁠
⁠
How has the ETF performed so far this year? Link in bio. (Check out CNBC Pro for 7 day for free!)

node.text:
Bitcoin topped $48,000 over the weekend, its highest level since May, but pared some of those gains on Monday.⁠
⁠
On Saturday, the digital coin hit $48,126.47, according to Coindesk data. (Around 9 a.m. ET on Monday, bitcoin was trading at $47,263.35.) Bitcoin’s rise lifted the value of the entire cryptocurrency market above $2 trillion on Saturday for the first time since mid-May, according to data from CoinMarketCap.⁠
⁠
What does one expert say investors should expect from bitcoin in the coming months? Link in bio.

node.text: The world was shocked this week by horrifying scenes of Afghans swarming the tarmac at Kabul’s international airport, grasping at their last chance to escape a country now overrun by the Taliban. 🔗 in today’s Story to read about how Afghanistan fell to the Taliban so quickly.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'Chaotic scenes at Kabul airport as Afghans and foreign nationals flee Taliban 10 CNBC'.

node.text:
Thousands of Afghans gathered on the tarmac at Kabul’s international airport in the hours after the Taliban captured the capital.⁠
⁠
The chaotic scenes show a desperate rush to escape the country.⁠
⁠
“If you don’t have a visa or passport, which the majority of Afghans don’t, you’re not going,” an analyst stuck in the country said.⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Dogecoin is the "strongest" cryptocurrency as a medium of exchange, Mark Cuban says CNBC'.

node.text:
Though dogecoin was created as a joke and its creators never intended for it to be taken seriously, Mark Cuban says it has a unique use case over other cryptocurrencies.⁠
⁠
“It’s a medium that can be used for the acquisition of goods and services,” Cuban tells @CNBCMakeIt. “The community for doge is the strongest when it comes to using it as a medium of exchange.”⁠
⁠
What does Cuban think the future holds for other cryptocurrencies like bitcoin and ethereum? Link in bio.
